From e2d54c79079d4ab8f5e23f6fc3ec61945fa3f010 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Saleh <saleh@emergegcc.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Apr 2026 21:37:37 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Warnings panel: central dashboard with one-click fixes + undo
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- New '🚩 Warnings' button in the toolbar. Shows a live count (e.g.
  '🚩 3 warnings') that updates on every renderSched, turning red when
  there are any issues.
- Click it to open a panel listing every warning across the week, grouped
  by day. Each row shows severity color (red/orange/grey), type label,
  car, message, and action buttons.
- One-click fixes for the structural/time issues:
    - Stranded teacher → '➕ Insert pickup' (adds auto-pickup after drop)
    - Orphaned pickup → '🗑 Delete pickup'
    - Early pickup → '⚡ Shift to correct time' (deletes wrong pickup and
      re-inserts after the drop's slot on same day/car)
- For ergonomic-only warnings (far student, long drive, double-drop gap,
  past-cutoff) each row has '👁 Jump' (switches day + scrolls + flashes
  the slot) and '🗑 Delete slot' (sends student(s) back to pool).
- Every fix snapshots SCHED first and shows a toast with an '↶ Undo' link
  that is active for 10 seconds. Clicking it restores the pre-fix state.
- slotWarnings() refactored to call a new slotWarningsStructured() that
  returns typed objects ({type, msg, data}). Old string-based callers
  still work via a wrapper for the existing 🚩 pop-up on slot cards.
- New allScheduleWarnings() walks every active day and car and returns
  a flat list tagged with d/cid/si/car for the panel.
- Smoke tests 18 + 19 verify the typed warning objects and the stranded
  → insert-pickup round trip. 19/19 passing.
